Gray-900 for the heading, gray-600 for body, blue-600 for the button. All pass their minimum contrast.

## Simple Check

Install a contrast checker browser extension. Look at three text-heavy elements in your current project. Any failing? Fix them now.

## Mom, That Shirt Doesn't Have Enough Contrast With My Hair!

- Body text minimum: gray-600 on white. Better: gray-700 or darker.
- Check buttons: white text needs blue-600 or darker background.
- Use DevTools or a checker. Your eyes lie.
- Don't optimize for light rooms or perfect vision. Accessible contrast works for everyone.
